<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Hi all, I'm a 38 enchanter on nameless.  All I can say is wow, this is a beautiful robe, especially on a high elf.  Decent AC, high INT, no its not all that common, though the price is down to 8kpp on nameless.  I wouldn't be at all surprised to see the prices of everything go up though, as soon as this whole duping thing is over.  In certain areas though, yes, this robe is common.  So what if I can walk into lower guk and half of the level 45+ people are wearing it, they're SUPPOSED to be wearing it.  I myself got it when I liquidated my rogue twink (yes, I will kick myself for this later) and got my enchanter some better gear.  The stats alone warrent the 8kpp pricetag, not to mention its rarity and how hard it is for a group of level 40ish people to camp.  To each her own, if you don't like it, don't buy it, don't camp it, STFU.<BR>
<BR>
Also, if you combine this with black boots and gloves (on a high elf, bear hide and gloves of gatecaller) it is just lovely.  Just keep your other gear in a bag and put it on when the you need it, just because incandescant gloves give high ac with some charisma, doesn't mean you have to wear the horrid looking things all the time =)<BR>
<BR>
